Source:  Loughnan Glossary
Author:  LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page:  23
Edition:
Quote:  to take a cut: to take out this portion. It needs a good man on a good horse to cut cows from their calves at foot, and, an even more delicate operation, to take a cut of ewes without mismothering them from their lambs.
